House Resolution 805
By: Representatives Willis of the 55th and Bell of the 75th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Ray Murray; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Ray Murray is a founding member of the Grammy Award-winning production
3 group Organized Noize whose work has been pivotal in establishing Southern hip-hop as a
4 dominant force in the music industry; and
5 WHEREAS, Organized Noize has been the creative genius behind iconic tracks like every
6 song on Outkast's Southernplayalisticadillacmuzik, all the tracks on Goodie Mob's Soul
7 Food, TLC's "Waterfalls," En Vogue's "Don't Let Go," and many other timeless hits, with
8 their distinct sound deeply rooted in the cultural spirit of Georgia's "Red Clay"; and
9 WHEREAS, Ray is a proud resident of Fulton County, having grown up in the West End and
10 later moving from Sylvan Hills to East Point in 1987, where he met Sleepy Brown and the
11 late Rico Wade, and together they formed the legendary trio that has shaped the landscape
12 of hip-hop; and
13 WHEREAS, Ray is now celebrating the 25th anniversary of his major contributions to
14 Outkast's groundbreaking album Stankonia, an album that changed the course of music
15 history; and
