16 WHEREAS, Ray continues to be a passionate advocate for the development of musical
17 education and the arts, actively supporting youth programs like the Joseph B. Whitehead's
18 Boys & Girls Club to nurture the next generation of creative talent.
19 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
20 the members of this body recognize and commend Ray Murray for his monumental influence
21 on the music industry, his exceptional work in shaping Southern hip-hop, and his ongoing
22 dedication to supporting youth arts programs and education.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
24 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Ray
25 Murray.
